  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Begin soaking your rice in plenty of water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a medium saucepan, poach your lamb ribs in cardamom, and one garlic bulb (cut in half). Bring to the boil, removing the ‘scum’ as it boils. Drain and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the ends from your white onions and then make an incision halfway down not going past the core/middle."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a medium saucepan, on a low simmer, poach the onions in salted water for 10-15 mins. You should see the onion layers coming apart."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once soft, run cold water over the onions. Carefully remove each onion layer and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Prep your vine leaves by removing from the jar and rinsing in cold water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For your peppers, make a slit in each and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now that your vegetables are all ready, let’s start on the stuffing."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the rice and add to a large bowl. Add the lamb mince."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dry mix all the spices and 20g salt. Add to the rice and lamb along with the sunflower oil, half your pomegranate molasses, tamarind paste, and water."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Stuff your onions and peppers."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roll your vine leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now we can begin layering the pot."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a medium saucepan, place the lamb ribs at the bottom of the pot. Layer on your vine leaves, followed by the onions and then, finally, the baby peppers."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely slice one bulb of garlic and add to the saucepan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drizzle with the remaining pomegranate molasses and the juice of your lemons."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Season with salt and add water until it reaches the peppers."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring to a boil with the lid on. Then bring down to a simmer until the water has reduced. After 1 hour, remove from the heat and you’re ready for that dolma reveal."
    }
  ],
